## Summary

### Always Fix
- ‚ùå Security warnings
- ‚ùå Hardcoded credentials
- ‚ùå SQL injection risks
- ‚ùå Production workflow errors

### Usually Fix
- ‚ö†Ô∏è Error handling (production)
- ‚ö†Ô∏è Retry logic (external APIs)
- ‚ö†Ô∏è Input validation (public webhooks)
- ‚ö†Ô∏è Rate limiting (high volume)

### Often Acceptable
- ‚úÖ Error handling (dev/test)
- ‚úÖ Retry logic (internal APIs)
- ‚úÖ Rate limiting (low volume)
- ‚úÖ Query limits (small datasets)

### Always Acceptable
- ‚úÖ Known n8n issues (#304, #306, #338)
- ‚úÖ Auto-sanitization warnings
- ‚úÖ Metadata completeness (auto-fixed)

**Golden Rule**: If you accept a warning, document WHY.

